                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17811017-47-victim445 t17811017-47-viclabel232"></join>. On Tuesday, the 25th of September, the prisoner came to my house, and called for a pint of beer. When he was gone, we missed a pint pot off the seat where he had sat. I went out after him, and found him in the street, with my pot in his breeches.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was in distress. I went to the parish, and they would give me only sixpence, to get me a lodging.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17811017-47-verdict234" type="verdictDescription">
